## Summary

Ports the approved popover fix from
[self-evolving/lean-workspace-template#23](https://github.com/self-evolving/lean-workspace-template/pull/23)
at `89449ac`.

This PR is stacked on the canvas-performance PR #4 because it extends that branch's explicit
Quartz test runner.

- delays popover dismissal by 300 ms after leaving an internal link;
- cancels pending dismissal when the popover is hovered or receives focus;
- prevents stale timers from clearing a newly active popover;
- removes the canvas-only `pointer-events: none` rule so canvas previews can be interacted with;
- adds focused fake-timer coverage for dismissal, cancellation, stale-target protection, and rescheduling;
- includes the focused suite in explicit CI test-file runs.

The delayed dismissal is implemented in the shared Quartz popover layer, so non-canvas internal-link
popovers receive the same brief linger behavior.

## Scope

Exactly five files differ from PR #4:

- `quartz/components/scripts/popover.inline.ts`;
- `quartz/components/scripts/popoverClearScheduler.ts`;
- `quartz/components/scripts/popoverClearScheduler.test.mjs`;
- `quartz/components/styles/popover.scss`;
- `scripts/run-tests.mjs`.

All five are byte-identical to the approved template PR head.

## Validation

Passed with Node 22.17.0:

- focused popover scheduler tests: 4/4;
- full test discovery: 127/127;
- explicit CI Quartz invocation: 29/29;
- `npm run check`;
- clean-cache `npm run build`;
- `git diff --check`.

